data.title: What's going on at St. Mark's around Great Wyrley
meta_keywords: What's going on at St. Mark's
data.meta_description: What's going on at St. Mark's. Sunday 20th December. Thursday 24th December. Friday 25th December. Sunday 27th December. Weekly Pewsheet. Great Wyrley Parish.
data.text:
- 4th Sunday of Advent

6:30pm - Traidtional Lessons & Carols Service

Come and hear some Christmas readings and sing your favourite carols.

Afterwards enjoy a glass of mulled wine and mince pie.

- Christmas Eve

5pm - Carols round the Christmas Tree

A family friendly fun service involving lots of people and singing favourite carols.

11:30pm - Midnight Communion Service

Come and welcome in Christmas Day as we celebrate the birth of Jesus The Christ.

- Christmas Day

8am - Holy Communion

A Book of Common Prayer said service in traditional language.

10am - Family Communion

Come and celebrate Christ's birth as part of the Church's family in this modern language service with carols.
